column3: Tea bags individually wrapped in foil pouches. Freshness stays in. Air and moisture stays out. America's classic. Family tea blenders since 1945. Refreshing peppermint - pure & simple. All natural. Because mama moved the pony stable. In 1945, Ruth Bigelow was trying to establish a market for her new product, Constant Comment Tea. This was no easy task. One evening, Ruth was sharing her discouragement when her sister said - Remember-Mama moved the pony stable. As a child, Ruth's family had a pony named Bottoms, who lived in a sturdy stable outside of the Bigelow's home. When her father announced one day that the family was moving to the other side of Providence, the children lamented that Bottoms would never be happy without his stable. Though she knew it would be a great deal of work, finally, Ruth's mother said, The stable will come. The move commenced and they all paraded across Providence. It took four rented horses and six hired workmen to move the stable while Bottoms trotted behind them. Well-wishers, advice-givers and hecklers followed. On the Bigelow's first night in a strange new house in Providence, Bottoms had his familiar stable. As Ruth relived these scenes, the significance of her sister's comment was clear: if she wanted to do something badly enough she could. Whenever Ruth was feeling defeated, she would remind herself, Mama moved the pony stable. This always gave her the courage and ingenuity to carry on. - The Bigelow family. Unlock the freshness. Every time I would mention spearmint to Ruth she showed no interest. So I decided to take matters into my own hands. My husband David and I went behind closed doors and started experimenting. We wanted a smooth flavorful premium tea to partner with a subtle spearmint flavor. We tried tea after tea to find the perfect combination. Then we set out to find a spearmint grown in America. We tried several spearmints and fell in love with one from a farm out west. Once we created the perfect blend we had to figure out how to share with Ruth our new invention. To be honest, we were nervous. That is when David came up with the perfect plan. So, on Mother's Day that year we were celebrating with Ruth and gave her a gift. The Family Tradition Continues From the beginning, my grandmother Ruth Bigelow made the holidays a very special time at Bigelow Tea. She would personally select and then wrap the perfect gift for each and every employee. Ruth would hand deliver the gifts and extend her gratitude to all for their hard work and dedication to her little tea company. This tradition would continue on as our company grew with my parents selecting different gifts for me and my sister Lori to hand out to each employee. Our mother would dress us in matching outfits that she had hand sewn. I was so excited to be a part of this ritual. With each delivery I insisted on hugging and kissing every employee! As the company continues to grow we have found new ways to honor this tradition. Gifts are still given out, but it is now the children and grandchildren of our employees that are the recipients at our annual North Pole Party. For three generations giving smiles and thanks to our employees and their families has become a Bigelow holiday tradition. We hope our tea delights you. column1: Bigelow Green Tea, with Peach, Bags
column3: Tea bags individually wrapped in foil pouches. Freshness stays in. Air and moisture stays out. America's classic. Family tea blenders since 1945. A sweet peach note enhances our delicate green tea. Healthy antioxidants. All natural. The Connecticut Tea Party. In 1955, Bigelow Tea moved from New York to Connecticut. Soon afterwards, back-to-back hurricanes hit! Connecticut rivers, including the Norwalk River, where the new factory resides, rose up over 35 feet, moving over 50 miles an hour. Ruth and David Bigelow worried desperately about their fledging 10 year old business. When they finally reached the factory, they saw their own version of the Connecticut Tea Party. The building was flooded and all of their tea had washed down the river. Although devastated, Ruth (in her 60's) and David (in his late 70's), were determined not to give up their dream. Turning to an employee, Ruth asked How long till we can get back in business? It took tremendous effort to get everything in order again. However, with the help of their creditors who extended them whatever they needed, the Bigelows were back in business in just a few months. Their tenacity is the foundation of what our company is built on. Our family learned two lessons that we still adhere to: always pay your bills on time, and when you get knocked down, just get right back up! - The Bigelow family. Unlock the freshness. Here's the key - we use a special foil pouch to protect your tea from any air, moisture and surrounding aromas. So open and enjoy the unparalleled flavor, freshness, aroma of Bigelow Tea everywhere we go! Caff-o-Meter Content Per Serving: Green tea 25-50 mg. Our Promise: We're fully committed to your satisfaction and we love to hear from you! When you do call, please share the code number on this box with the Consumer Service crew. bigelowtea.com. Reason to Love: One of the most widely used and well-loved herbs of the world, we adore chamomile for its mildly bittersweet, flowery taste and its ability to soothe and calm the body, mind and spirit. Our chamomile is a cut above the common chamomile you'll find in most teas. Made from only the white and yellow, tiny, daisy-like flowers (no stems and leaves here), we think of our chamomile tea as a cup of peaceful, easy feelings-plain and simple. Taste: Fragrantly floral, honey-like and bittersweet. It's not easy being blue - chamomile's soothing properties can be attributed, in part, to the essential oil, which, when extracted, is an amazing blue color. Concentrated in the flowering tops, we look for chamomile with high amounts of this blue oil, so every cup of our tea will surely soothe your system. Don't worry though - your tea won't turn blue. We source this ginger primarily from India, where it thrives in a humid, tropical climate. Ginger's rhizome - or underground, horizontal stem (commonly called a root) - sprouts the plant's first shoots within two weeks of planting. column3: Herbal Supplement. New look. Same great tea! Since 1974. Created by herbalists. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. Tabebuia impetiginosa. Personality: Gorgeous, strong and enigmatic. Herbal Power: Used historically by the indigenous peoples of South America and modern day herbalists. Reason to Love: We love this amazingly beautiful, flowering tree, also known as Pink Ipe or Pink Lapacho, due to its stunning pinkish, purple trumpet-like flower. Traditional healers have been using the inner bark for hundreds of years. Only more recently has this cherished herb made its way into the herbal traditions of the West. Taste: Earthy taste - woody, tannic and slightly bitter. Organic Pau d'Arco: When it comes to history, Pau d'Arco is full of it. With a reputation for use dating back well before the time of the Incas (that was a good 700 years ago or so), Pau d'Arco is well-known and loved throughout South America. It is widely used as an ornamental tree and can be found lining the streets of many South American cities - it's even the national tree of Paraguay! It's also well-loved for its hard, durable wood and was used to make the hunting bows of the indigenous people who inhabited the rainforests of the Amazon. Only the inner bark is used by traditional healers and modern day herbalists. The bark is dried before being made into tea. www.traditionalmedicinals.com. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. America's classic. Family tea blenders since 1945. Our First Home: Where Bigelow Tea was born. Sometime in 1942 or '43, my mom and dad decided they wanted to start a tea business. At the time, we lived in a small apartment in Manhattan. They felt strongly that, for the company to be a success, they needed a home where they could begin. Searching the local streets, they found a brownstone, just off of Second Avenue, which was in terrible disrepair. Optimistic, they bought it with the last of their life savings, and replastered and repainted it themselves. It was in this home in 1945, where my mom and dad opened the doors to the new Bigelow Tea Company. Little could they have imagined that their dream would one day grow to be America's No. 1 specialty tea company! - David Bigelow. Son Don't Tell Your Mother: Back in 1945, when the Bigelow Tea company first started, Ruth Bigelow and the family could only afford a single-color label for her tea. To help spruce up the package, David Jr. and David Sr. would sit together each night, hand-painting the two ladies on the original label. Each morning, they would put the tea into the family station wagon and sell it store by store. One night, David Sr. turned to David Jr. and said Son, don't tell your mother, but I don't think this company is ever going anywhere. Almost 70 years later, David Jr. still smiles at the memory, and is grateful that his father was mistaken. Today, Bigelow Tea is the specialty tea leader in the US. America's family tea blenders since 1945. Now bursting with more raspberry taste. Thank Goodness for that Little Jar: When Ruth Campbell Bigelow started Bigelow Tea in 1945, the going was tough. She had created a wonderful tea, Constant Comment, but now had to try to sell it, one store at a time. One day, she visited a store that had begun to successfully sell her tea. The shopkeeper shared with her that he had been opening up a container to allow his consumers to enjoy the tea's amazing aroma. One whiff and they were sold! he said. Ruth immediately started including in each case an extra little jar of Constant Comment labeled open and whiff. Shops across the country placed this whiffing jar by their cash registers. This would prove to be a defining moment that helped grow our family's tea company into the success it is today. Thanks goodness for that little jar! - The Bigelow Family. Unlock the freshness. column3: Tea bags individually wrapped in foil pouches. Freshness stays in. Air and moisture stay out. A full bodied rich smooth tea perfect any time of day. All natural. America's classic. Family tea blenders since 1945. Thank goodness for that little jar - When Ruth Campbell Bigelow started Bigelow Tea in 1945, the going was tough. She had created a wonderful tea, Constant Comment, but now had to try to sell it, one store at a time. One day, she visited a store that had begun to successfully sell her tea. The shopkeeper shared with her that he had been opening up a container to allow his consumers to enjoy the tea's amazing aroma. One whiff and they were sold! he said. Ruth immediately started including in each case an extra little jar of Constant Comment labeled open and whiff. Shops across the country placed this whiffing jar by their cash registers. This would prove to be a defining moment that helped grow our family's tea company into the success it is today. Thank goodness for that little jar! - The Bigelow family. column3: Herbal Supplement. Naturally caffeine free herbal tea. Fair Wild. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. USDA organic. Herbal teas. Created by herbalists. Since 1974. Non-GMO Project verified tea bag & string. Rubus idaeus. Personality: Gently nurturing and a friend of women. Herbal Power: Supports healthy menstruation, tones the uterus and may be used for menstrual cramps. Reason to Love: Of course, the delectable fruit of rubus idaeus is a well-known and well-loved summer treat, but it's the raspberry leaf you'll find in the this tea. With a silvery under leaf that is reminiscent of the moon's glow, European and Native American women have used raspberry leaf for thousands of years for menstrual support, menstrual cramps and during pregnancy as a healthy tonic to help prepare the womb for childbirth. We love this tea for its gently nurturing properties, and its robust taste, which is reminiscent of a delicate and mildly fruity black tea. Taste: Full-bodied, like a fine black tea (without the caffeine!). A prolific plant that does well in temperate environments, some of our favorite raspberry leaf grows wild and is gathered by hand in the Gorazde collection region of Bosnia and Herzegovina. Gathered by a group of collector families, the young leaves are best when hand-picked in early summer before the fruits develop. Sustainable wild collection represents an important source or income for these families who live on small plots of land nestled amongst the gorgeous rolling hills and meadows of the region. www.traditionalmedicinals.com. We've Got the Right Stuff: We raise the bar. The quality standard of the herbs we use is hard to pronounce, difficult to meet, and it's what makes us different, better. We're not ashamed to say it. Pharmacopoeial: It's the only quality standard our herbalists can rely on when blending teas for your health and wellness. Certified by the California Certified Organic Farmers (CCOF). Non-GMO project verified tea bag & string. Eucalyptus globulus. Magnolia sprengeri. Personality: Wise and lively, a breath of fresh air. Herbal Power: Gently shakes things up and helps you Breathe Easy. Reason to Love: One of our original teas, Breathe Easy tea has been supporting people for over four decades. This enduring classic combines the best of Western herbalism with ancient traditional Chinese wisdom resulting in a unique blend that warms and engages the senses. Eucalyptus, fennel and licorice are combined with bi yan pian extract, a traditional Chinese formula of 11 different herbs. We love this aromatic and fragrant blend that soothes with its warm and spicy taste. Taste: Balanced, bittersweet, with hints of aromatic citrus. One of our sources of eucalyptus is from Chile, where the leaves are carefully harvested to preserve the essential oil-which is responsible for the characteristic aroma and taste of eucalyptus, which you'll notice as you steep this tea. Our formula also includes the traditional Chinese herbal blend bi yan pian (bee-yahn pee-yahn), which features the ancient magnolia flower. Evolved before bees existed in the world, magnolia flowers developed to encourage pollination by beetles, and have been used in Chinese and Japanese herbal traditions for centuries. www.traditionalmedicinals.com. column3: Tea bags individually wrapped in foil pouches. Freshness stays in. Air and moisture stay out. Blend of chamomile & mint to calm & soothe. All natural. America's classic. Family tea blenders since 1945. The Connecticut Tea Party: In 1955, Bigelow Tea moved from New York to Connecticut. Soon afterwards, back-to-back hurricanes hit! Connecticut rivers, including the Norwalk River, where the new factory resided, rose up over 35 feet, moving over 50 miles an hour. Ruth and David Bigelow worried desperately about their fledging 10 year old business. When they finally reached the factory, they saw their own version of the Connecticut Tea Party. The building was flooded and all of their tea had washed down the river. Although devastated, Ruth (in her 60's) and David (in his late 70's), were determined not to give up their dream. Turning to an employee, Ruth asked How long till we can get back in business? It took tremendous effort to get everything in order again. However, with the help of their creditors who extended them whatever they needed, the Bigelows were back in business in just a few months. Their tenacity is the foundation of what our company is built on. Our family learned two lessons that we still adhere to: always pay your bills on time, and when you get knocked down, just get right back up! - The Bigelow family. column3: Made right. Thick, rich and loaded with brown sugar and molasses, this sauce is dripping with sticky sweetness that you're gonna love. Great with beef, chicken, pork, fish. For recipes and more, visit Stubbsbbq.com or find us on Facebook. Born here. Stubb loved a good road trip. Sometimes he'd cook up a bunch of food, load it into his Cadillac and head east to Memphis or Nashville. column3: Made right with vinegar and spices. All-natural. If you were ever lucky to watch Stubb hard at work tending to the meat on the pit, you'd likely have seen him with a short-handled mop in hand. Stubb would mop the meat with this special basting sauce as it was cooking to keep it moist and tender. So use Stubb's Moppin' Sauce and you too can say Ladies and Gentlemen, I'm a cook - just like Stubb! Simply baste meats with the zesty blend of vinegar, pepper and paprika of Stubb's Moppin' Sauce as it cooks. This will keep moisture in, prevent charring and keep the meat tender. column1: Uncle Mattys Food Sauce, Signature Red
column3: All natural. No preservatives. No MSG. Uncle Matty's Food Co's Signature Red Sauce is a family recipe that has been carefully crafted in an effort to refine the bold flavors of various BBQ regions. We started with acids, native to the Carolinas, and an all natural group of sweeteners inspired by the South Georgia BBQ pits. We then paired it with our unique Texas-inspired tomato blend and an array of hand-selected spices. The result is a simple yet complex BBQ sauce that creates an extremely deep flavor profile along with a perfect balance from start to finish. column3: Since 1897. All natural ingredients. Gluten free. Our savory blend of coarsely-milled brown mustard and zesty horseradish. There really was a Peter Koops, a young Dutch adventurer who left his shipping business in the Netherlands for a new life in America. He began with a hand-crank mustard mill and a horse-drawn cart, selling mustard by the ladle to loyal customers. Our packaging and delivery systems have changed since then, but our carefully made stone-ground recipes are the same. Certified gluten-free. www.koopsmustard.com. My daughter, Gillian, was diagnosed with Celiac disease in 1992 when she was six years old. Learning what foods were not safe was an exhausting process. Many additives are wheat-based and found in most common foods. For me, an executive chef, finding a palatable bread that would not fall apart in Gillian's lunch box was my first mission. Many years of research and experimentation resulted in not only bread, but a whole line of healthy foods that Gillian has given a thumbs up to. Gillian's Foods is proud to offer what we think is the best wheat-free, gluten-free croutons on the market today. Look for all our other products in your store, or order online at www.gilliansfoods.com. Enjoy! - Chef Bob. Great with soup too! Visit us at: www.gilliansfoods.com. Lea & Perrins combines the finest ingredients sourced from around the world and ages them to perfection to produce a flavor unmatched for over 175 years. The Famous Paper Wrap: In 1837, Lea & Perrins first began exporting Worcestershire Sauce around the world by boat. The lengthy and often rough sea voyages caused some of the bottles to break. The practice of wrapping each bottle in a paper wrap was devised to protect the bottles and prevent damage during transit. Although no longer technically necessary, the custom has endured, and the paper wrap has come to symbolize the rich heritage and premium quality of Lea & Perrins, a tradition dating back to 1835. column1: Bee City Honey, Bears, Pure Raw
Luquire Family Foods Grits, Stone Ground
column3: From the fine folks at Carolina Creole. carolinacreole.com. Perfect complement to Carolina creole. Our Story: For decades we have been serving family and friends some of the tastiest creole on the Carolina coast. Now, after countless requests, we're glad to share Carolina Creole in convenient, meal in-a-jar bottles. The perfect complement to Carolina Creole? Luquire Family Foods Stone Ground Grits, of course. Our all-natural grits hail from Greenwood, South Carolina where our family started milling grits and flour in the late 1930s. Whether it's for your next plate of creole or a staple of a hearty breakfast, like us, we think you'll agree that our stone ground grits are sure to become a family favorite. Just add shrimp, chicken, sausage or vegetables to a pan of simmering Carolina Creole, serve over Luquire Family Foods Stone Ground Grits or Enriched Long Grain Rice and you've got a delicious simple to prepare, gourmet meal. - P. column3: 30% less sodium than our Original Worcestershire Sauce. All natural. Same premium quality since 1835. Unwrap the possibilities. Since 1835, Lea & Perrins has been the one truly authentic brand of Worcestershire Sauce. Lea & Perrins combines the finest ingredients sourced from around the world and ages them to perfection to produce a flavor unmatched for over 175 years. The Famous Paper Wrap: In 1837, Lea & Perrins first began exporting worcestershire sauce around the world by boat. The lengthy and often rough sea voyages caused some of the bottles to break. The practice of wrapping each bottle in a paper wrap was devised to protect the bottles and prevent damage during transit. Although no long technically necessary, the custom has endured, and the paper wrap has come to symbolize the rich heritage and premium quality of Lea & Perrins, a tradition dating back to 1835. For more recipes, please visit our website at www.leaperrins.com. Lea & Perrins Reduced Sodium Worcestershire Sauce: 45 mg sodium, Regular Lea & Perrins Worcestershire Sauce: 65 mg sodium. column1: Geraldines Cheese Straws, Baked, Aged Cheddar
column3: My famous traditional southern recipe! All natural. It's how we entertain! Some years ago a Southern gentleman, Turner Holmes Cunningham, won the hand of Geraldine of Oaks, North Dakota, and whisked her off to his mini-plantation. Geraldine bore Turner Holmes three sturdy sons and one daughter, Catherine. Turner Holmes prospered and became high school principal, the most scrutinized position in town. One weekend when Catherine's youth had reached full flower, the elder Cunninghams journeyed to Atlanta. Catherine opened their home to the young ladies and gentlemen of Newnan where she served her mother's cheese straws made from a secret recipe. The party promptly became the wildest festivity that the fair town had ever witnessed. When the Cunninghams returned, the town was in an uproar over the irreparable damage that had been wreaked upon its youth. How to save the day? Geraldine knew the power of her cheese straws. People have been known to bargain with the devil to get their lips around just one. She baked her delicate fingers to the bone. The children went door-to-door delivering those potent little peace offerings. After a few bites the townspeople not only forgave the Cunninghams, but found themselves dancing wildly in the town square. So if you want to turn your dignified gathering into a get down bash, serve up Geraldine's Bodacious Cheese Straws. No preservatives. What makes Geraldine's Cheese Straws so bodacious? It's all about the cheese! Look at the ingredient list. Our No. 1 item is Cheese. Most cheese snacks have flour as the first ingredient. Geraldine's uses premium quality cheese, lots of it, mixed with other all natural ingredients then baked crisp for a truly Bodacious taste sensation. It's the ultimate cheese snack! The Coconut Secret Story: When both our parents learned they were diabetic, my brother and I were deeply inspired to search the world for pure, raw, truly delicious, low glycemic products. We were rewarded and blessed beyond expectations, in our discovery of the traditional products made from the sap of the wondrous coconut tree. It is our great joy to be able to share with you the gifts of these exceptional ingredients. - Leslie and Randy. Health Secrets of Coconut Aminos: When the coconut tree is tapped it produces a highly nutrient rich sap that exudes from the coconut blossoms. This sap is raw, very low glycemic, an abundant source of 17 amino acids, minerals, vitamins, and has a nearly neutral pH. A comparison between coconut tree sap and soy, shows that coconut sap contains 2-14 times the amino acid content of soy. Small batches ensure that our organic, low glycemic Coconut Aminos, made from this natural sap, is a raw enzymatically alive product aged and blended with sun dried, mineral-rich sea salt, hand gathered from pristine waters near the southern islands of the Philippine coast. Recipe Tips: Soy-Free Seasoning alternative for use like soy sauce in salad dressings, marinades, sautes, and with sushi! This delicious product does not have a coconutty flavor. column3: Reggae Country Style. Special blend. If you have questions or comments on this product, call toll free 1-800-915-5678 weekdays,10-6 eastern standard time. Www.JCSKitchen.com. Recyclable. 100% Caribbean owned and formulated. Jerk is popular method in Jamaica of barbecuing well-seasoned pork, chicken, and fish. Jerk can be traced to the Coromantee hunters of pre-Slavery West Africa who passed it on to the Maroons. They would mast seasoned pork over hot coals in earthen pits that were covered with Pimento branches. Boston Beach, an area on the northeastern Jamaica, is internationally famous for jerk pork. Reggae style. Authentic Jamaican recipe. Packed in USA.Show LessPimento branches. Boston Beach, an area on the northeastern Jamaica, is internationally famous for jerk pork. Reggae style. column3: The Gold Standard of Bar-Be-Que: Bar-be-que is something we southerners take very seriously, and here in the Lowcountry of South Carolina we love our mustard-based bar-be-que sauce. Our bar-be-que sauce is a touch of bar-be-que heaven, and we have the awards to prove it. My father, Big Joe Bessinger, created this delicious bar-be-que sauce back in the 1930's and ever since he - and now I - have packed 'em into our restaurants for that heavenly taste. You might not have the time or the equipment to make bar-be-que like we do, but with a jar of Thomas Bessinger's Original Golden Recipe, you can come pretty close. Use it for basting, dipping and marinating pork, ribs, chicken, beef or even burgers. Give it a try and savor some Lowcountry flavor. Y'all come! - Thomas Bessinger. Quality since 1922. Ideal for seasoning fish, seafood, meat & vegetables. Centuries ago, necessity forced the Maroon peoples in the mountains of Jamaica to develop a method to preserve and season meat. Thus was born a way of food preparation called jerk that today defines one distinct element of the Jamaican culinary experience. Jerked chicken, pork, fish and vegetables are equally at home around the backyard grill, at the street dance, on the beach and as part of an elegantly served white glove experience. Today, that unique combination of escallions, ginger, scotch bonnet peppers, all-spice, garlic and nutmeg that is the basis of jerk cooking, comes to you perfectly blended, ready to use as you create in your own home, the authentic Jamaican jerk experience. www.gracefoods.com. Individually wrapped. Nobody treats you like Nonni's. From Family Tradition to Artisan Bakery Delights: The story of Nonni's began in the Tuscan town of Lucca, Italy. That's where our founder's beloved grandmother - known as Nonni - first baked her delicious biscotti for family and friends using only real, hand picked ingredients she found at her local market. When he opened his artisan bakery in 1988 - called Nonni's, of course - he followed his grandmother's recipes and uncompromising quality standards while adding a few tasty twists of his own. Today our bakers are inspired to follow Nonni's old world traditions in preparing a variety of delicious delights using real ingredients you might find at a farmer's market. No artificial flavors or preservatives. Just one taste and you will understand that nobody treats you like Nonni's! Real ingredients. No compromises. Real, wholesome ingredients. Baked by real bakers. Made with real eggs, sugar and butter. Baked twice for a light, crunchy texture that's delicately sweet and satisfying. column3: Made with almonds, walnuts and a hint of anise. Real dark chocolate. No artificial flavors. 110 calories. Artisan baked. Est 1988. Italian inspired. Real ingredients. No compromises. Nobody treats you like Nonni's. From Family Tradition to Artisan Bakery Delights: The story of Nonni's began in the Tuscan town of Lucca, Italy. That's where our founder's beloved grandmother - known as Nonni - first baked her delicious biscotti for family and friends using only real, hand picked ingredients she found at her local market. When he opened his artisan bakery in 1988 - called Nonni's, of course - he followed his grandmother's recipes and uncompromising quality standards while adding a few tasty twists of his own. Today our bakers are inspired to follow Nonni's old world traditions in preparing a variety of delicious delights using real ingredients you might find at a farmer's market. No artificial flavors or preservatives. Just one taste and you will understand that nobody treats you like Nonni's! Real ingredients. No compromises. Real, wholesome ingredients. Baked by real bakers. Made with real eggs, sugar and butter. Baked twice for a light, crunchy texture that's delicately sweet and satisfying. Old fashioned ginger cookies. Baked with pride. The great taste you love since 1941. Murray Old Fashioned Ginger Snaps take you back to days gone by. They remind you of a time when wheelbarrow races and skipping stones were the order of the day. This tasty, crispy, authentic ginger cookie is a great refreshment with an ice-cold glass of milk or as a warm-up on a cool day with a hot cup of coffee. Murray Old Fashioned Ginger Snaps cookies have a taste reminiscent of simpler times. Packaged in the familiar brown bag, they have been enjoyed by Americans for generations. In the 1940s John L. Murray, Sr. started making his great-tasting cookies with just a single oven. As the popularity of his delicious cookies grew, he purchased an old patrol wagon and turned it into the very first Murray delivery truck. His dedication and enthusiasm for making irresistible cookies has helped form a long and lasting relationship with cookie lovers everywhere. For over 70 years, families have enjoyed filling their cookie jars with the great taste of Murray cookies. We still offer the same successful recipe of great taste and great value, and we invite you to enjoy all of our delicious flavors. Produced with genetic engineering. Questions or comments? A Chocolate Indulgence You Can Feel Good About: It all began when Sheila G, a passionate chocolate-loving baker, took a treasured family recipe for fudge brownies and baked her way into a thriving business. You may have tasted one of her rich, dense squares of heaven at some of our nation's finest restaurants and theme parks. Like many brownie aficionados, Sheila is particularly fond of the crispy edges. In fact, she took great joy in walking through the bakery, gathering the brittle batter off the sides of the sheet pans as the brownies cooled in their racks. And that is where Sheila found her inspiration for Brownie Brittle - a thin, award-winning treat with a rich brownie taste, an amazing cookie crunch and only 120 calories per serving. Deliciously versatile, Sheila G's Brownie Brittle is great right out of the bag, as well as crumbled over ice cream, yogurt, cereal, and more. column3: Sweden's most loved pepparkaka! By appointment to H.M. the King of Sweden. Since 1929. Annas is a brand of the Lotus Bakeries Group, which specialises in high quality bakery and biscuit products. All natural ingredients. 0 g trans fat per serving. Some things you just don't change. A lot has happened since Anna Karlsson baked her very first Swedish Thin in her little backstreet bakery in downtown Stockholm, Sweden. Today her Swedish Thins, or Peppparkakor in Swedish, are known all over the world. It is still her wonderful mixture of spices: cinnamon, sugar, and cloves. They are still carefully crafted, always using traditional baking trays which gives the Swedish Thins their delicate crispness. Perhaps that's why Annas are Sweden's most loved Pepparkaka - and have been since 1929. Treat your family to Annas Swedish Thins, and make this cherished Swedish tradition your own. column3: Made with almonds, toffee and milk chocolate. Real milk chocolate. No artificial flavors. 110 calories. Est 1988. Artisan baked. Italian inspired. Real ingredients. No compromises. Individually wrapped. Nobody treats you like Nonni's. From Family Tradition to Artisan Bakery Delights: The story of Nonni's began in the Tuscan town of Lucca, Italy. That's where our founder's beloved grandmother - known as Nonni - first baked her delicious biscotti for family and friends using only real, hand picked ingredients she found at her local market. When he opened his artisan bakery in 1988 - called Nonni's, of course - he followed his grandmother's recipes and uncompromising quality standards while adding a few tasty twists of his own. Today our bakers are inspired to follow Nonni's old world traditions in preparing a variety of delicious delights using real ingredients you might find at a farmer's market. No artificial flavors or preservatives. Just one taste and you will understand that nobody treats you like Nonni's! Real ingredients. No compromises. Real, wholesome ingredients. Baked by real bakers. Made with real eggs, sugar and butter. Baked twice for a light, crunchy texture that's delicately sweet and satisfying. The Famous Amos Cookies Story - Wally Amos: Originally, Wally Amos baked delicious cookies in his home to share with his friends and family. In 1975, he was inspired by a passed-down family recipe and perfected the ultimate chocolate chip cookie. With the commitment to use only the best ingredients, he then started his own company. Wally's homemade-tasting cookies with semi-sweet chocolate chips and flavorful nuts were so special they became famous just by word of mouth. Today, Famous Amos cookies still meet these high expectations and are enjoyed by all true cookie lovers. Enjoy the special recipe and homemade taste that made Amos famous! - Wally Amos. column3: Rich brownie taste with a cookie crunch. Made with natural ingredients. Only 120 calories per serving. Enjoy! XO, Sheila G. Facebook; Twitter; Pinterest; Instagram. A Chocolate Indulgence You Can Feel Good About: It all began when Sheila G, a passionate chocolate-loving baker, took a treasured family recipe for fudge brownies and baked her way into a thriving business. You may have tasted one of her rich, dense squares of heaven at some of our nation's finest restaurants and theme parks. Like many brownie aficionados, Sheila is particularly fond of the crispy edges. In fact, she took great joy in walking through the bakery, gathering the brittle batter off the sides of the sheet pans as the brownies cooled in their racks. And that is where Sheila found her inspiration for Brownie Brittle - a thin, award-winning treat with a rich brownie taste, an amazing cookie crunch and only 120 calories per serving. Deliciously versatile, Sheila G's Brownie Brittle is great right out of the bag, as well as crumbled over ice cream, yogurt, cereal, and more. Like the crispy edge of a gourmet brownie, Sheila G's Brownie Brittle satisfies your chocolate desires with fewer calories than other sweet snacks. So, crave away with these rich pieces of chocolate decadence you can feel good about. Proud supporter of Cookies for Kids' Cancer. browniebrittle.com. 1-800-BROWNIE (1-800-276-9643). column1: Buds Best Cookies Cookies, Chocolate Chip, Bite Size
column3: Lots of real chocolate chips! Little cookie. Big taste. Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than forty years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But, besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. Because of our commitment to give our customers the highest quality cookies at the lowest possible price, you have my word - Bud's Best is the best! - Bud Carson. column3: Perfect for tiramisu. Savoiardi, commonly known as Lady Fingers, are delightful and delicately light cookies from Italy that have been enjoyed by Italians for generations. Eaten as a snack alongside a glass of milk, children love their simple goodness. Adults too enjoy nibbling on them between sips of espresso or cappuccino. The Italians have invented wonderous desserts using them in creations like Tiramisu. Tiramisu is an Italian delight that has of late become a most fashionable dessert. Its origins have been traced back to Siena where it had been called Zuppa Del Duca or The Duke's Soup. The dessert became very popular in Florence in the nineteenth century where the English people who lived in the town renamed it Zuppa Inglese or English Soup. The dessert has several variations and has always enjoyed great popularity over the years regardless of the name. Made with mascarpone cheese, delicate lady fingers and laced with strong espresso coffee, Tiramisu literally translates to pick me up which refers to the inevitable energizing boost this dessert will provide. www.alessifoods.com. column1: Buds Best Cookies Cookies, Pecan Supremes, Bite Size
column3: Little cookie. Big taste. Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than forty years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But, besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. Because of our commitment to give our customers the highest quality cookies at the lowest possible price, you have my word: Bud's Best is the best! - Bud Carson. column3: Southampton, NY. Uniquely crispy. Deeply delicious. Gluten free. Founder approved. Created by: Kathleen King. Craft baked. Texture: Crispy thin scrumptious. A little bake shop in every bite. The Bake Shop Way: What makes Tate's Bake Shop Cookies so deeply delicious? It's something we call the bake shop way. It started when 11-year-old Kathleen King began baking cookies to sell at her parent's farmstand. Her love of baking and dedication to quality made her crisp, buttery cookies legendary in Southampton, and were the inspiration for what eventually became Tate's Bake Shop. While our bake shop is still local favorite, our cookies have won a loyal following from coast to coast, with Kathleen's intuition, passion and principles guiding everything we do. column1: Pirouline Wafers, Artisan Rolled, Chocolate Hazelnut
column3: All natural. Since 1860. Enjoy as a snack with coffee, tea, ice cream, after dinner drinks, family and friends. Whether you are sitting back and relaxing by yourself, spending time with close friends or simply on the run, your creme de pirouline is the perfect way to transport you to your destination and indulge in the swirl of life. This flavorful chocolate hazelnut is a perfect combination of our finest all natural cocoa with the delicious flavor of hazelnuts wrapped in our toasted pirouline wafer and sealed with our signature swirl. Make Pirouline (peer-o-lean) a tradition in your home. Since 1860, the DeBeukelaer family has been baking premium Belgium biscuits and wafers. Pirouline is the only national brand of rolled wafers actually made in America. It's a cylindrical world please recycle. column3: Southampton, NY. Uniquely crispy. Deep delicious. Founder Approved: Craft Baked: crispy; thin; scrumptious - Kathleen King. A little bake shop in every bite. The Bake Shop Way: What makes Bake Shop Cookies so deeply delicious? It's something we call the bake shop way. It started when 11-year-old Kathleen King began baking cookies to sell at her parent's farmstand. Her love of baking and dedication to quality made her crisp, buttery cookies legendary in Southampton, and were the inspiration for what eventually became Tate's Bake Shop. While our bake shop is still a local favorite, our cookies have won a loyal following from coast to coast, with Kathleen's intuition, passion and principles guiding everything we do. So enjoy one of our deeply delicious cookies and experience the bake shop way. Find more craft-baked goodness at TatesBakeShop.com. Facebook. Twitter. Pinterest. Instagram. column1: Nonnis Thin Addictives Almond Thins, Dark Chocolate Cherry Almond
column3: 7 freshness packs of 2. Est. 1988. Artisan baked. Italian inspired. Lightly sweet & crunchy. Real dark chocolate. No artificial flavors. 70 calories per 2-pack. Nobody treats you like Nonni's. From family tradition to artisan bakery delights. The story of Nonni's began in the Tuscan town of Lucca, Italy. That's where our founder's beloved grandmother - known as Nonni - first baked her delicious biscotti for family and friends using only real, hand picked ingredients she found at her local market. Today our bakers are inspired to follow Nonni's old world traditions in preparing a variety of delicious artisan delights using real ingredients you might find at a farmer's market. No artificial flavors or preservatives. Nonni's THINaddictives are a wholesome snack baked with the same uncompromising quality standards to create an exceptionally light, crispy one of a kind taste and texture. Each deliciously addictive thin is filled with: whole almonds; real fruits; wheat flour. Just one taste and you will understand that nobody treats you like Nonni's! So many delicious ways to enjoy! On-the-Go: Enjoy healthy, wholesome snacking anywhere. It's loaded with real fruits & nuts, lightly sweetened and only 70 calories per pack. On-a-Plate: Instead of crackers or chips, enjoy the crispy crunch of THINaddictives with cheese, nut butter or preserves. Or serve with fruit, dips or guacamole. On-the-Top: Crumble on top of ice cream or yogurt for an incredibly delicious crunchy 'mix-in' like no other. If you have any questions or comments, please call us at 1-877-295-9604. Visit our website at www.nonnis.com.Show Lessrket. column3: Simply mi-delicious. 0 g trans fat. Peanut free. Taste why they're mi-delicious. For over 65 years, we've used the same simple methods to bake our cookies. Why change, when healthy ingredients let us make such delicious treats? Samuel Midel invented these wholesome cookies because he wanted to make sure his children got real nutrition when they snacked. We're happy to keep the same promise to you, no fancy packaging, just simple, old-fashioned delicious goodness. Mi-del Ginger Snaps are made with organic unbleached wheat flour, canola oil and natural ginger. Our cookies are sweetened with organic dehydrated cane sugar, which is less refined than most other sugars and sweeteners. It is milled within 24 hours after the cane sugar is harvested. Using 10 fewer processing steps than refined white sugar, our cane sugar is pressed and crystallized to maintain its purity and wholesomeness. panosbrands.com. midelcookies.com. column1: Buds Best Cookies Cookies, Ginger Snaps, Old Fashioned
column3: Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than fifty-five years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But, besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. Because of our commitment to give our customers the highest quality cookies at the lowest possible price, you have my word: Bud's Best is the best! - Bud Carson. Facebook: Become our fan on Facebook. column3: Little cookie. Big taste. Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than 40 years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. Because of our commitment to give our customers the highest quality cookies at the lowest possible price, you have my word: Bud's Best is the best! - Bud Carson. column3: Lightly sweet & crunchy. Real dark chocolate. No artificial flavors. 80 calories per 2-pack. Artisan baked. Est 1988. Italian inspired. Freshness packs of 2. Nobody treats you like Nonni's. From Family Tradition to Artisan Bakery Delights: The story of Nonni's began in the Tuscan town of Lucca, Italy. That's where our founder's beloved grandmother - known as Nonni first baked her delicious biscotti for family and friends using only real, hand picked ingredients she found at her local market. Today our bakers are inspired to follow Nonni's old world traditions in preparing a variety of delicious artisan delights using real ingredients you might find at a farmer's market. No artificial flavors or preservatives. Nonni's THINaddictives are a wholesome snack baked with the same uncompromising quality standards to create an exceptionally light, crispy one of a kind taste and texture. Each deliciously addictive thin is filled with: whole almonds; real fruits; wheat flour. Just one taste and you will understand that nobody treats you like Nonni's! So many delicious ways to enjoy! On-the-Go: Enjoy healthy, wholesome snacking anywhere. It's loaded with real fruits & nuts, lightly sweetened and only 80 calories per pack. On-a-Plate: Instead of crackers or chips, enjoy the crispy crunch of Thin Addictives with cheese, nut butter or preserves. Or serve with fruit, dips or guacamole. On-the-Top: Crumble on top of ice cream or yogurt for an incredibly delicious crunchy mix-in like no other. If you have any questions or comments, please call us at 1-877-295-9604. column1: Buds Best Cookies Cookies, Oatmeal, Bite Size
column3: Made with California raisins. Little cookie. Big taste. Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than forty years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But, besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. Because of our commitment to give our customers the highest quality cookies at the lowest possible price, you have my word - Bud's Best is the best! - Bud Carson. Buds Best Cookies Cookies, Strawberry Cremes, Bite Size
column3: Little cookie. Big taste. Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than forty years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But, besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. Because of our commitment to give our customers the highest quality cookies at the lowest possible price, you have my word: Bud's Best is the best! - Bud Carson. column1: Mi del Ginger Snaps, Gluten-Free, Swedish Style
column3: Perfect for those with gluten sensitivity. 0 g trans fat. Dairy free. Peanut free. Taste why they're mi-delicious. For over 65 years, we've used the same simple methods to bake our cookies. Why change, when healthy ingredients let us make such delicious treats? Samuel Midel invented these wholesome cookies because he wanted to make sure his children got real nutrition when they snacked. We're happy to keep the same promise to you, no fancy packaging, just simple, old-fashioned delicious goodness. We developed gluten-free Ginger Snaps specifically for those with gluten intolerance. First identified in the late 1800s as a dietary concern, gluten intolerance (celiac disease) requires diet modification since the source of the protein gluten is wheat, rye and barley. Made with all natural ingredients, these delicious Mi-Del Ginger Snaps will satisfy the snacking urges of anyone, while meeting the dietary requirements of those who are gluten sensitive. Try the wholesome goodness of all our delicious gluten-free cookies. Ginger Snaps. Cinnamon Snaps. Chocolate Chip Cookies. Pecan Cookies. Arrowroot Cookies. Chocolate Sandwich Cookies. column3: Sweden's most loved pepparkaka! Since 1929. By appointment to HM the King of Sweden. 0 g trans fat per serving. Some things you just don't change. A lot has happened since Anna Karlsson baked her very first Swedish Thin in her little backstreet bakery in downtown Stockholm, Sweden. Today her Swedish Thins, or pepparkakor in Swedish, are known all over the world. But the recipe Anna used back then hasn't changed one bit. It is still her wonderful mixture of ingredients and flavors. They are still carefully crafted, always using traditional baking trays which gives the Swedish Things their delicate crispness. Perhaps that's why Annas are Sweden's most loved pepparkaka - and have been since 1929. Annas Almond Swedish Thins have a cinnamon spice with a subtle almond flavor in a deliciously crispy, perfectly thin delicate cookie. Treat your family to Annas Swedish Thins and make this cherished Swedish tradition your own. Find Inspiration at: www.annas.se. Try all our other flavors! www.annas.se. column3: Sweden's most loved pepparkaka! Since 1929. By appointment to HM the King of Sweden. All natural ingredients. 0 g trans fat per serving. Some things you just don't change. A lot has happened since Anna Karlsson baked her very first Swedish Thin in her little backstreet bakery in downtown Stockholm, Sweden. Today her Swedish Thins, or Pepparkakor in Swedish, are known all over the world. But the recipe Anna used back then hasn't changed one bit. It is still her wonderful mixture of ingredients and flavors. They are still carefully crafted, always using traditional baking trays which gives the Swedish Thins their delicate crispness. Perhaps that's why Annas are Sweden's most loved pepparkaka - and have been since 1929. Annas Orange Swedish Thins have a subtle orange flavor in a deliciously crispy, perfectly thin delicate cookie. Treat your family to Annas Swedish Thins and make this cherished Swedish tradition your own. Find Inspiration at: www.annas.se. Try all our other flavors. www.annas.se. column1: Newmans Own Organics Cookies, Hermits, Cinnamon
Newmans Own Organics The Second Generation Cookies, Fig Newmans
column3: Fruit filled cookies made with organic figs. Wheat free. Dairy free. Not a gluten-free product. A Figurative Theory: I think most people know about Adam and Eve's blunder in the garden, but my Pop has developed his own theory. I was in the middle of a peaceful breakfast when Pop bounded up the stairs with a sixty pound crate of ancient scrolls, talking to himself. It wasn't the apple, it was the figs, the figs! I stayed motionless hoping he'd wander off and talk to one of the dogs, when his hand reached out to stop me from eating my oatmeal. Nellie, these scrolls confirm my theory. When Adam and Eve used the fig leaves to cover up their own embarrassment and tossed the precious figs in the dirt, their act in the garden was cancelled. With one hand over my teacup and the other shaking my oatmeal spoon, he concluded his biblical theory, the apple incident, as far as I am concerned, was nothing compared to their wanton waste of the figs. This is why my Pop reveres the fig and I like to eat breakfast in my room. For my Pop's sake, I hope you , too, will revel in the divine quality of our Fig Newmans. Sincerely, Nell Newman. PS - The enjoyment of our Fig Newmans doesn't require an allegiance to my Pop's theory. Certified organic by Oregon Tilth. column1: Tates Bake Shop Cookies, White Chocolate, Macadamia Nut
column3: Uniquely crispy. Deeply delicious. Founder approved. Kathleen King. Craft baked. Crispy thin scrumptious. A little bake shop in every bite. The bake shop way. What makes Tate's Bake Shop cookies so deeply delicious? It's something we call the bake shop way. It started when 11-year-old Kathleen King began baking cookies to sell at her parent's farmstand. Her love of baking and dedication to quality made her crisp, buttery cookies legendary in Southampton, and were the inspiration for what eventually became Tate's Bake Shop. While our bake shop is still a local favorite, our cookies have won a loyal following from coast to coast, with Kathleen's intuition, passion and principles guiding everything we do. column3: Outrageously delicious cookies baked with love and passion. Fresh baked. Organic. Gluten-free. USDA organic. Indulge organically! It Started With a Dream. In 2009, I graduated from the Institute of Integrative Nutrition as a holistic nutritionist. Based on my education and passion for healthy living, I had a dream of creating a line of desserts for people who have a love for clean, organic foods, a healthy lifestyle and a sweet tooth for one of life's greatest indulgences - fresh baked treats! As a mom of four boys, I've always been passionate about home cooked meals that are delicious, nutritious, whole and organic. I strongly feel that dessert should be no exception. After weeks of researching the best of organic, gluten-free, kosher and non-GMO flours, nuts, fruits, dark chocolates, eggs and butter, my first winner was born - Chocolate Chip Love - an insanely delicious, gluten-free twist on a classic chocolate chip cookie. My boys and husband raved over them. And so, ginnybakes was born! Today, my first batch of cookies has grown into a line of gluten-free, organic or all natural, kosher, fresh baked cookies, biscottis, bars and bake mixes for everyone to enjoy. I am proud to say ginnybakes are free of preservatives, chemicals and refined sugars. Always looking for ways to enhance and improve fresh baked goods, I will continue to expand our vegan line, while also being conscious of the imminent importance of non-GMO products. I offer these from my heart with love and passion. XO Ginny. Paperboard packaging recyclable. SFI Certified sourcing. www.sfiprogram.org. Chocolate lovers rejoice! column3: Little cookie. Big taste. Cookies are in my blood. As a boy of 12 years old, working in my aunt's bakery, I knew that someday I wanted to own my own cookie factory. I've now been in the cookie business for more than forty years. My vision and dream of building the most modern cookie plant in the world came true in 1991. Of course, I've seen a lot of changes over the years - from selling cookies out of a jar for a penny each, to producing over a million cookies per hour. We even offer tours through the plant on our Cookie Train, so you can see for yourself how Bud's Best Cookies are made. But, besides their delicious taste, perhaps one of the greatest things about Bud's Best Cookies is they're bite-sized! That means they're perfect for kids of all ages. column3: Just the right amount of wrong. Naturally gluten-free. Certified gluten-free. column3: Since 1886. Chocolate covered cookies with crispy rice. Authentic Belgian recipe. The original. 100% all-natural. Without preservatives, colorings or artificial flavourings. The year is 1886 and in the small town of Lo in West Flanders, Jules Destrooper for the first time prepares the perfect dough for his delicious butter biscuits. The original recipes, based on the very best natural ingredients, remain until this very day a strictly guarded family secret. The superior quality of the biscuits has not only brought Jules Destrooper gold medal awards but also the official recognition as Purveyor to the Belgian Royal Household. Delicious chocolate covered biscuits with crispy rice made with only the best milk and dark Belgian chocolate. The unique combination of rice and a fine layer of chocolate makes this biscuit a real treat for both biscuit and chocolate lovers. column3: Fresh baked. Organic. Gluten-free. Outrageously delicious cookies baked with love and passion. USDA organic. GF: Certified Gluten free. Indulge organically! It started with a dream. In 2009, I graduated from the Institute of Integrative Nutrition as a holistic nutritionist. Based on my education and passion for healthy living, I had a dream creating a line of desserts for people who have a love for clean, organic foods, a healthy lifestyle and a sweet tooth for one of life's greatest indulgences - fresh baked treats! As a mom of four boys, I've always been passionate about home cooked meals that are delicious, nutritious, whole and organic. I strongly feel that dessert should be no exception. After weeks of researching the best of organic, gluten-free, kosher and non-GMO flours, nuts, fruits, dark chocolates, eggs and butter, my first winner was born - Chocolate Chip Love - an insanely delicious, gluten free twist on a classic chocolate chip cookie. My boys and husband raved over them. And so, ginnybakes was born! Today, my first batch of cookies has grown into a line of gluten-free, organic or all natural, kosher, fresh baked cookies, biscottis, bars and bake mixes for everyone to enjoy. I am proud to say ginnybakes are free of preservatives, chemicals and refined sugars. Always looking for ways to enhance and improve fresh baked goods, I will continue to expand our vegan line, while also being conscious of the imminent importance of non-GMO products. I offer these from my heart with love and passion. - xo ginny. Paperboard packaging - Recyclable. SFI - certified sourcing. www.sfiprogram.org. column1: Newmans Own Organics The Second Generation Cookies, Fig Newmans
column3: Fruit filled cookies made with organic figs. Low fat. Nell Newman. Pa Newman. A figurative theory. I think most people know about Adam and Eve's blunder in the garden, but my pop has developed his own theory. I was in the middle of a peaceful breakfast when pop bounded up the stairs with a sixty pound crate of ancient scrolls, talking to himself. It wasn't the apple, it was the figs, the figs! I stayed motionless hoping he'd wander off and talk to one of the dogs, when his hand reached out to stop me from eating my oatmeal. Nellie, these scrolls confirm my theory. When Adam and Eve used the fig leaves to cover their own embarrassment and tossed the precious figs in the dirt, their act in the garden was cancelled. With one hand over my teacup and the other shaking my oatmeal spoon, he concluded his biblical theory, The apple incident, as far as I am concerned, was nothing compared to their wanton waste of the figs. This is why my pop reveres the fig and I like to eat breakfast in my room. For my pop's sake, I hope you, too, will revel in the divine quality of our Fig Newmans - Sincerely, Nell Newman. PS - The enjoyment of our Fig Newmans doesn't require an allegiance to my pop's theory. Certified organic by Oregon Tilth. Cookies made in USA.Show Lessop me from eating my oatmeal. column1: Lance Quick Starts Breakfast Biscuit Sandwiches, Blueberry Muffin

column3: Fresh baked. Organic. Gluten free. Outrageously delicious cookies baked with love and passion. USDA organic. Certified gluten-free. Indulge organically! It started with a dream. In 2009, I graduated from the Institute of Integrative Nutrition as a holistic nutritionist. Based on my education and passion for healthy living, I had a dream of creating a line of desserts for people who have a love for clean, organic foods, a healthy lifestyle and a sweet tooth for one of life's greatest indulgences - fresh baked treats! As a mom of four boys, I've always been passionate about home cooked meals that are delicious, nutritious, whole and organic. I strongly feel that dessert should be no exception. After weeks of researching the best of organic, gluten-free, kosher and non-GMO flours, nuts, fruits, dark chocolates, eggs and butter, my first winner was born - Chocolate Chip Love - an insanely delicious, gluten-free twist on a classic chocolate chip cookie. My boys and husband raved over them. And so, ginnybakes was born! Today, my first batch of cookies has grown into a line of gluten-free, organic or all natural, kosher, fresh baked cookies, biscottis, bars and bake mixes for everyone to enjoy. I am proud to say ginnybakes are free of preservatives, chemicals and refined sugars. Always looking for ways to enhance and improve fresh baked goods, I will continue to expand our vegan line, while also being conscious of the imminent importance of non-GMO products. I offer these from my heart with love and passion. Xo. - ginny. Recyclable paperboard packaging. SFI: certified sourcing. www.sfiprogram.org. column3: All natural. Fresh baked. Organic. Gluten-free. USDA organic. Certified gluten-free. Indulge organically! It started with a dream. In 2009, I graduated from the Institute of Integrative Nutrition as a holistic nutritionist. Based on my education and passion for healthy living, I had a dream of creating a line of desserts for people who have a love for clean, organic foods, a healthy lifestyle and a sweet tooth for one of life's greatest indulgences - fresh baked treats! As a mom of four boys, I've always been passionate about home cooked meals that are delicious, nutritious, whole and organic. I strongly feel that dessert should be no exception. After weeks of researching the best of organic, gluten-free, kosher and non-GMO flours, nuts, fruits, dark chocolates, eggs and butter, my first winner was born - Chocolate Chip Love - an insanely delicious, gluten-free twist on a classic chocolate chip cookie. My boys and husband raved over them. And so, ginnybakes was born! Today, my first batch of cookies has grown into a line of gluten-free, organic or all natural, kosher, fresh baked cookies, biscottis, bars and bake mixes for everyone to enjoy. I am proud to say ginnybakes are free of preservatives, chemicals and refined sugars. Always looking for ways to enhance and improve fresh baked goods, I will continue to expand our vegan line, while also being conscious of the imminent importance of non-GMO products. I offer these from my heart with love and passion. Xo. - ginny. Recyclable paperboard packaging. SFI: certified sourcing. www.sfiprogram.org. Go nuts for our organic indulgence! Dark organic chocolate chips dance with plump organic macadamia nuts to create another tasty gluten-free twist on a classic cookie! Indulge organically with ginnybakes! Ginnybakes products are produced with love and care in a gluten free facility. ginnybakes are formulated to avoid genetically engineered ingredients. US law does not allow the use of genetically engineered ingredients or seed in products labeled as organic. Certified organic by Quality Assurance International. www.ginnybakes.com. column1: Mi del Chocolate Snaps, Swedish Style
column3: Simply Mi-Delicious. 0 g trans fat. Peanut free. Taste Why They're Mi-Delicious: For over 65 years, we've used the same simple methods to bake our cookies. Why change, when healthy ingredients let us make such delicious treats? Samuel Midel invented these wholesome cookies because he wanted to make sure his children got real nutrition when they snacked. We're happy to keep the same promise to you - no fancy packaging, just simple, old-fashioned delicious goodness. Mi-Del Chocolate Snaps are made with organic unbleached wheat flour, canola oil and natural cocoa powder. Our cookies are sweetened with organic dehydrated cane sugar, which is less refined than most other sugars and sweeteners. It is milled within 24 hours after the cane is harvested. Using 10 fewer processing steps than refined white sugar, our cane sugar is pressed and crystallized to maintain its purity and wholesomeness. Try the wholesome goodness of all our Mi-Del cookies. panosbrands.com. midelcookies.com. Product of Canada.Show Lesswith organic unbleached wheat flour, canola oil and natural cocoa powder. column3: It's simple: no short-cuts, just 100% commitment to quality and 12 g protein per serving. USDA organic. Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org. Arrowhead Mills brand was born in the Texas Panhandle back in 1960. We've grown, but we haven't changed how we do things. We're still using our same trusted milling process and building long-term relationships with our organic growers, working with them face-to-face, day-to-day. Hard work, honesty, kindness, and business with a handshake - that's our process. That's the Arrowhead way. It's how we bring the awesome goodness of the land to your table and we're real proud of it. Green Lentils are nutritious as well as delicious. When combined with rice you get a complete protein. Enjoy them with brown rice in a casserole or season with garlic and onions for a tasty side dish. Great for soups and mashing into patties! Excellent source of fiber. Excellent source of iron. Visit www.Arrowheadmills.com for information on all our delicious products. Certified organic by quality assurance international (QAI). Comments?
